# Command k9s

## What does this command do:

K9s provides a terminal UI to interact with your Kubernetes clusters

## Installed from

For Fedora install using: sudo dnf install k9s
For Raspberry Pi install using: curl -sSfL https://github.com/derailed/k9s/releases/latest/download/k9s_Linux_arm64.tar.gz | tar -xz -C ~/.local/bin/ k9s
For Mac install using: brew install derailed/k9s/k9s

## Command path

For Fedora run: /usr/bin/k9s
For Raspberry Pi run: ~/.local/bin/k9s
For Mac run: /opt/homebrew/bin/k9s

## Command documentation

Docs can be found at https://github.com/derailed/k9s

## Command options

# Launch k9s (uses current kubeconfig context)
k9s

# Launch in a specific namespace
k9s -n <namespace>

# Launch across all namespaces
k9s -A

# Launch with a specific kubeconfig context
k9s --context <context>

# Launch in read-only mode (disables all mutations)
k9s --readonly

# Launch with write mode (overrides readOnly config)
k9s --write

# Open directly on a resource type
k9s -c pods
k9s -c deployments
k9s -c nodes

# Show runtime info (config paths, log file location, etc.)
k9s info

# Print version
k9s version

# Display/UI flags
k9s --headless       # hide header
k9s --crumbsless     # hide breadcrumb trail
k9s --logoless       # hide logo
k9s --splashless     # skip splash screen
k9s --invert         # invert skin (dark↔light)

# Logging
k9s -l debug                        # set log level (error, warn, info, debug)
k9s --logFile /tmp/k9s.log          # override log file path

# Set refresh rate (seconds, default 2)
k9s -r 5

# --- TUI keyboard shortcuts ---

# Navigation
?              Help / key binding reference
esc            Go back / cancel
ctrl-c / :q    Quit k9s

# Jump to a resource view (type in the command bar)
:pods          View pods (also: :po)
:deployments   View deployments (also: :deploy)
:services      View services (also: :svc)
:nodes         View nodes (also: :no)
:namespaces    View namespaces (also: :ns)
:configmaps    View configmaps (also: :cm)
:secrets       View secrets
:ingresses     View ingresses (also: :ing)
:events        View events (also: :ev)
:crds          View custom resource definitions
:ctx           Switch kubeconfig context
:ns            Switch namespace

# Filtering (within a resource list)
/              Enter filter mode — type to filter by name
!              Inverse filter
/label=value   Filter by label

# Resource actions (on selected row)
d              Describe resource
e              Edit resource (opens in $EDITOR)
y              View YAML
l              View logs (pods only)
s              Shell into container (pods only)
shift-f        Port forward
ctrl-d         Delete resource
ctrl-k         Kill resource (SIGKILL)
c              Copy resource name to clipboard
x              Decode secret value
f              Full-screen log toggle

# Log view shortcuts (while in log view)
w              Toggle line wrap
f              Toggle full-screen
t              Toggle timestamps
0-9            Filter by container (0 = all)
ctrl-s         Save logs to screen dump dir

# Column and sort
ctrl-w         Toggle wide columns
ctrl-e         Toggle header
1-9            Sort by column number

# Shell completion
k9s completion bash | sudo tee /etc/bash_completion.d/k9s
k9s completion zsh > ~/.zsh/completions/_k9s
